Many non-Ukrainian refugees, such as Africans, Afghans and Yemenis are reportedly facing discrimination and poor treatment while leaving Ukraine and crossing its border to seek asylum in a third country, especially in Europe. Some EU nations are more willing to welcome white Ukrainian refugees with open arms. Credits: Editor: Yuan Xin Designer: Wang Shiqi Senior producer: Wei Wei Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)